{{Infobox person | image =Stan Yanevski.doyler79.jpg | imagesize = | caption = | birth_name = Stanislav Ianevski | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1985|05|16}} | birth_place = [[Sofia]], [[Bulgaria]] | death_date = | death_place = | years active = 2005âpresent | occupation = Actor | spouse = }} '''Stanislav Ianevski''' ({{lang-bg|Ð¡ÑÐ°Ð½Ð¸ÑÐ»Ð°Ð² Ð¯Ð½ÐµÐ²ÑÐºÐ¸}}; born May 16, 1985) is a [[Bulgarians|Bulgarian]] actor, known for playing [[Viktor Krum]] in the 2005 film ''[[Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire (film)|Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire]]''.
Ianevski was born in [[Sofia, Bulgaria]] and has lived in [[England]] (for five years)<ref name=ref>[http://www.novinite.com/view_news.php?id=55852 Stanislav Ianevski: Proud to be Bulgarian<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> and [[Israel]].<ref>[http://www.comingsoon.net/news/topnews.php?id=10507 The New Blood From Goblet of Fire - Coming Soon.net<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://www.snitchseeker.com/harry-potter-news/stanislav-ianevski-sugar-magazine-29429/ Stanislav Ianevski in Sugar Magazine - SnitchSeeker.com<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> While attending [[Mill Hill School]] in the [[United Kingdom]], Ianevski had no particular acting aspirations and was not a drama student. He had only auditioned for ''[[Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire (film)|Harry Potter]]'' after being spotted by [[Fiona Weir]], a casting director who prompted him to attend an acting workshop, which resulted in his casting as [[Viktor Krum]], a [[Bulgaria]]n character in the [[Harry Potter]] series. He was selected from 600 others, most of whom had auditioned in [[Sofia, Bulgaria]]. [[Harry Melling (actor)|Harry Melling]], who played the part of [[Dudley Dursley]], attended Mill Hill School at the same time.
Ianevski's casting was announced in June 2004. During filming, he befriended fellow ''Harry Potter'' actors [[Robert Pattinson]] and [[Emma Watson]]. He also starred in ''[[Hostel 2]]'', the sequel to [[Eli Roth]]'s film ''[[Hostel (2005 film)|Hostel]]''. He reprised his role as Viktor Krum in ''[[Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows (films)|Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows]]'' Part 1.<ref name=krum-doge-tlc>{{cite news|url=http://www.the-leaky-cauldron.org/2009/7/19/deathly-hallows-updates-stan-as-krum-returns-doge-is-cast-and-more|title=Deathly Hallows Updates: Krum Returns, Doge is Cast and More|date=2009-07-19|accessdate=2009-07-20|publisher=The Leaky Cauldron}}</ref> However, his sequences were cut from the final product, despite appearing in several photos.
